&lt;p&gt;Today I want to share with you the history of the development of a device for controlling a multi-apartment intercom using the Zigbee protocol.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once upon a time I had an automatic doorphone opener based on: ESP8266, a module for two relays (16A) and a transistor with a strapping.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All this was collected on a bunch of wires and snot made of hot melt glue and looked something like the second photo.



